    {
        "content": "<p>Hm, looks like <code>simp</code> cannot apply <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Data/Set/Basic.html#Set.union_eq_right\">Set.union_eq_right</a> if the goal is <code>t = s ∪ t</code>.<br>\nWe could add <code>Set.right_eq_union : t = s ∪ t ↔ s ⊆ t</code> to mathlib, but maybe we could fix <code>simp</code> to treat <code>=</code> as symmetrical and work the same regardless of order? Tbh, I though that <code>simp</code> already does that.</p>",
        "id": 568572585,
        "sender_full_name": "Jakub Nowak",
        "timestamp": 1768640323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>simp works best if you keep to idiomatic Lean, in particular meaning that complex expressions go on the LHS.</p>",
